{
  "text": "COMIX extends the approach described in [CITATION_1] where a collection of dialogue motivators is iteratively tested and, whenever the test for a motivator succeeds, the motivator's associated dialogue action is performed. In COMIX, a dialogue motivator's test, or applicability conditions, may refer to information from the CBPS. Whereas in Abella and Gorin's approach, a motivator is associated with one action, in COMIX a motivator can be realized through one of several alternative dialogue actions; selection of the action depends upon information from the CBPS. Whenever at least one motivator applies, COMIX takes dialogue initiative.",
  "citation_candidates": [
